'''Martin Perscheid''' (born February 16, 1966, in [[Wesseling]], [[Germany]]) is a German [[cartoonist]]. His drawing style resembles that of [[Gary Larson]].
His works have been published since 1994 in various [[Germans|German]] newspapers and magazines, since 1996 under the title "''Perscheids Abgründe''" (“Perscheid's Abyss”). Of his many honors, he was winner of the [[Max and Moritz]] prize of 2002 for the best German-language Cartoon Series, as well as the "''Kulturplakette''" (Culture Award) from his hometown of Wesseling.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bullspress.de/site/modules/comics.php?_cookie_try=1&area=showfeature&feature=news_id:18|title=Perscheids ABGRÜNDE}}</ref>
